l told the steward. Just watch.

972
01:22:25,816 --> 01:22:29,172
- lf you will come this way, sir.
- l'm going to have lunch.

973
01:22:29,256 --> 01:22:31,326
Yes. Another table has
been arranged for you.

974
01:22:32,736 --> 01:22:35,967
- Arranged? Who arranged it?
- Right over here, sir.

975
01:22:47,176 --> 01:22:48,768
Now he will see how we feel.

976
01:22:49,656 --> 01:22:53,968
Dr. Schumann, they have placed
Herr Freytag at another table.

977
01:22:57,376 --> 01:23:01,335
Herr Rieber, you are a real
anti-Semite. l don't know any Jews.

978
01:23:01,416 --> 01:23:03,327
l don't know anything
about them at all.

979
01:23:03,416 --> 01:23:06,567
l'm not an anti-Semite.
How can you say that?

980
01:23:06,656 --> 01:23:07,975
l'm very fond of the Arabs.

981
01:23:08,056 --> 01:23:11,571
l lived among them for a while and
found them to be very good people.

982
01:23:12,176 --> 01:23:14,565
You have not said a word, Dr.
Schumann.

983
01:23:14,656 --> 01:23:16,408
What do you think about..?
- Excuse me.

984
01:23:20,176 --> 01:23:21,894
Doctor has heart trouble.

985
01:23:23,056 --> 01:23:26,731
Do you suppose we should send
to inquire after him?

986
01:23:30,576 --> 01:23:31,725
Schumann.

987
01:23:33,336 --> 01:23:37,807
Schumann. ls that not a Jewish name?

988
01:23:39,176 --> 01:23:40,575
My wife is Jewish.

989
01:23:42,496 --> 01:23:44,248
l told that American woman.

990
01:23:45,256 --> 01:23:47,975
- She must have told them.
- Now come, have some wine.

991
01:23:48,816 --> 01:23:50,408
lt's Niersteiner Domtal.

992
01:23:51,496 --> 01:23:55,250
Why be upset? The company is
much better at this table..

993
01:23:55,336 --> 01:23:56,564
..l can assure you.

994
01:23:56,656 --> 01:24:00,649
When Glocken isn't smoking one
of his foul-smelling cigars.

995
01:24:03,376 --> 01:24:07,255
You know l don't mind not being
seated at the captain's table.

996
01:24:07,776 --> 01:24:10,813
Perhaps because l was never
invited in the first place.

997
01:24:11,496 --> 01:24:14,408
Those pious hypocrites.

998
01:24:15,816 --> 01:24:19,809
- Why do you take it? - l have
been taking it for a long time.

999
01:24:19,896 --> 01:24:25,573
Oh, yes, he has. He has 2000 years
of suffering behind him.

1000
01:24:26,176 --> 01:24:27,894
Well, l'm not going to take it.

1001
01:24:28,496 --> 01:24:32,250
A little patience. A
little understanding.

1002
01:24:32,376 --> 01:24:34,412
The world's getting
better all the time.

1003
01:24:34,816 --> 01:24:36,647
As my Aunt Rebecca used to say..

1004
01:24:36,736 --> 01:24:39,250
l don't give a damn what your
Aunt Rebecca used to say.

1005
01:24:47,416 --> 01:24:51,329
Do you think any of you are
any better Germans than l am?

1006
01:24:53,376 --> 01:24:54,570
Do you?

1007
01:24:59,576 --> 01:25:02,886
Yes. Yes, l have a Jewish wife.

1008
01:25:04,816 --> 01:25:08,252
She's Jewish. Let me
tell you about her.

1009
01:25:09,896 --> 01:25:13,172
She'd never hurt anyone in her life.

1010
01:25:16,176 --> 01:25:17,575
Anyone.

1011
01:25:20,056 --> 01:25:23,969
You.. You good, middling people.

1012
01:25:24,496 --> 01:25:26,726
You aren't fit to be in
the same world as her.

1013
01:25:28,336 --> 01:25:32,329
l saw some of you in the chapel this
morning. You kneel there and pray.

1014
01:25:32,416 --> 01:25:34,327
You pretend that you
are good people.

1015
01:25:36,256 --> 01:25:37,769
Good people?

1016
01:25:39,256 --> 01:25:42,646
You can't even exist without
your prejudices.

1017
01:25:43,896 --> 01:25:45,887
And the worst thing about you is..

1018
01:25:47,496 --> 01:25:51,250
..that you don't even
recognize what you are.

1019
01:25:52,256 --> 01:25:53,575
You..

1020
01:26:04,256 --> 01:26:08,169
Sometimes l think, in spite
of how much you understand..

1021
01:26:08,576 --> 01:26:10,168
..it's enough already.

1022
01:26:11,656 --> 01:26:12,805
What's going on?

1023
01:26:14,376 --> 01:26:16,571
They moved Herr Freytag from
the captain's table..

1024
01:26:16,656 --> 01:26:18,248
..because his wife is Jewish.

1025
01:26:20,816 --> 01:26:22,374
And it's my fault.

1026
01:26:23,056 --> 01:26:26,412
l had to tell that dreadful Brunhilda
to stop her from chattering on so.

1027
01:26:27,496 --> 01:26:31,569
So stupid of me. He's
such a nice man.

1028
01:26:33,736 --> 01:26:35,806
l'd no idea this was
going to happen.

1029
01:26:37,896 --> 01:26:41,650
- You're not gonna cry,
are you? - Of course not.

1030
01:26:42,976 --> 01:26:44,409
l never cry.

1031
01:26:49,816 --> 01:26:51,647
What do they got against the Jews?

1032
01:26:53,496 --> 01:26:55,805
Back home, we don't have anything
against the Jews.

1033
01:26:56,336 --> 01:26:58,975
Hell, l never even saw
a Jew till l was 15.

1034
01:27:00,496 --> 01:27:04,250
Maybe you were too busy lynching
Negroes to take time out for the Jews.

1035
01:27:27,976 --> 01:27:30,809
Why don't you ring for the steward?
He might give you something.

1036
01:27:30,896 --> 01:27:34,252
l have been ringing! Ringing!
Ringing! Ringing!

1037
01:27:34,336 --> 01:27:37,567
A fellow gave these pills
to me in Tangiers.

1038
01:27:37,656 --> 01:27:42,332
He had a theory that seasickness has
something to do with the eardrums.

1039
01:27:43,776 --> 01:27:44,891
You know, Lowenthal?

1040
01:27:44,976 --> 01:27:46,250
Yes?

1041
01:27:47,576 --> 01:27:49,726
You are really not
such a bad fellow.

1042
01:27:49,816 --> 01:27:51,249
You think so?

1043
01:27:51,336 --> 01:27:56,569
These statements that l make, you
mustn't take them personally.

1044
01:27:56,656 --> 01:27:57,884
No, of course not.

1045
01:27:57,976 --> 01:28:02,254
lt is the march of history. History
is beyond us, Lowenthal.

1046
01:28:05,656 --> 01:28:06,771
Feel better?

1047
01:28:08,056 --> 01:28:09,728
- A little. - Good.

1048
01:28:10,656 --> 01:28:13,966
You know, the thing l can't understand
is why you want to go back to Germany.

1049
01:28:14,056 --> 01:28:17,173
l would not want to be
where l was not wanted.

1050
01:28:17,256 --> 01:28:19,326
Why don't you go back
to your own country?

1051
01:28:19,416 --> 01:28:22,249
Germany is my country. My
father was born in Germany.

1052
01:28:22,336 --> 01:28:24,566
And my grandfather was
born in Germany.

1053
01:28:24,736 --> 01:28:29,252
As a matter of fact, where are you
from? l can't place your accent.

1054
01:28:29,336 --> 01:28:31,975
You speak German like no
one l have ever heard.

1055
01:28:32,056 --> 01:28:35,253
The last 20 years of my life
were spent in Germany.

1056
01:28:36,176 --> 01:28:37,575
Austria?

1057
01:28:39,416 --> 01:28:40,565
Near the border.

1058
01:28:41,496 --> 01:28:42,815
That's what l thought.

1059
01:28:42,896 --> 01:28:44,966
Lowenthal, you know it is
a historical fact that..

1060
01:28:45,056 --> 01:28:47,331
..the Jews are the basis
of our misfortunes.

1061
01:28:47,416 --> 01:28:48,735
- Of course. - You agree?

1062
01:28:48,816 --> 01:28:52,252
Of course. The Jews and
the bicycle riders.

1063
01:28:52,416 --> 01:28:56,250
Bicycle riders? Why
the bicycle riders?

1064
01:28:57,056 --> 01:28:58,330
Why the Jews?

1065
01:29:47,976 --> 01:29:50,729
- Hey, what's going on?
- Man overboard!

1066
01:29:50,896 --> 01:29:53,330
Man overboard!

1067
01:29:53,416 --> 01:29:55,247
Man overboard!

1068
01:29:55,336 --> 01:29:57,167
Hey, man overboard!

1069
01:30:32,176 --> 01:30:35,327
- Get her out of here! - Take
her to our cabin, please.

1070
01:30:41,336 --> 01:30:42,564
Turn him over.

1071
01:31:10,816 --> 01:31:12,374
Can you understand it?

1072
01:31:13,176 --> 01:31:16,771
A man jumps from a moving ship at
night, in the middle of the ocean.

1073
01:31:16,896 --> 01:31:19,364
And is drowned to save
the life of a dog.

1074
01:31:20,176 --> 01:31:21,814
Yes, l can understand.

1075
01:31:23,816 --> 01:31:24,885
Who was he?

1076
01:31:25,176 --> 01:31:29,647
He was a woodcarver. He carved
little animals with his pocketknife.

1077
01:31:41,336 --> 01:31:42,655
Come in, please.

1078
01:31:42,736 --> 01:31:44,806
Doctor, what can we do?

1079
01:31:45,656 --> 01:31:49,171
Well, you're doing all
that can be done.

1080
01:31:49,256 --> 01:31:51,770
- How did it happen? - Yeah.
How did it happen?

1081
01:31:51,856 --> 01:31:54,973
- He was thrown overboard.
-Who would do such a thing?

1082
01:31:56,336 --> 01:31:59,567
But look at him. He knows that
someone tried to drown him!

1083
01:31:59,896 --> 01:32:02,251
- His heart is broken. - Doctor!

1084
01:32:03,496 --> 01:32:04,770
You are not leaving?

1085
01:32:06,176 --> 01:32:09,327
Perhaps we could get him some
broth. Some hot broth.

1086
01:32:09,416 --> 01:32:12,647
Yes. You can give him some broth.
lt won't do any harm.

1087
01:32:12,736 --> 01:32:13,805
ls that all?

1088
01:32:14,576 --> 01:32:15,804
Yes, that's all.

1089
01:32:18,376 --> 01:32:19,968
The man who saved him is dead.

1090
01:32:25,056 --> 01:32:27,251
Did he say a man is dead?

1091
01:32:41,166 --> 01:32:42,645
l know how you feel.

1092
01:32:50,126 --> 01:32:52,720
No. You don't. You're
like the others.

1093
01:32:53,206 --> 01:32:55,640
You thought the captain was
justified in taking his knife away.

1094
01:32:55,726 --> 01:32:57,205
That's what you thought, wasn't it?

1095
01:32:57,646 --> 01:32:59,204
You were the one who felt
sorry for the captain.

1096
01:32:59,286 --> 01:33:00,878
That was you, wasn't it?

1097
01:33:02,646 --> 01:33:04,796
Why can't we be honest
with each other?

1098
01:33:04,886 --> 01:33:06,160
l don't know.

1099
01:33:11,886 --> 01:33:14,354
- Maybe we're afraid to be.
- Well, let's try.

1100
01:33:14,726 --> 01:33:16,637
Maybe we'd better try.

1101
01:33:20,646 --> 01:33:23,114
You say l hate your painting.
Well, l do.

1102
01:33:23,726 --> 01:33:26,559
Oh, God help me, but l do.
l don't know why.

1103
01:33:26,646 --> 01:33:29,797
You've said it. Maybe it's because
l'm not very good at it myself.

1104
01:33:29,886 --> 01:33:32,878
Or maybe.. just maybe it's because
it means so much to you..

1105
01:33:32,966 --> 01:33:34,797
..more than anything,
more than even me.

1106
01:33:37,806 --> 01:33:39,637
That's being honest, isn't it?

1107
01:33:43,886 --> 01:33:45,114
Yes, that's honest.

1108
01:33:50,286 --> 01:33:52,880
Well, l'll tell you something
that's even more sad.

1109
01:33:55,206 --> 01:33:57,162
l can't be what you want me to be.

1110
01:33:58,046 --> 01:34:00,879
And l know what you need. You need
someone just to be there..

1111
01:34:00,966 --> 01:34:02,638
..to deny herself for you.

1112
01:34:04,726 --> 01:34:07,365
David, l wish l could be
like that, but l can't.

1113
01:34:07,446 --> 01:34:10,358
- l just can't. - Jenny,
l know you can.

1114
01:34:13,046 --> 01:34:14,957
Well, it means leaving
me with nothing.

1115
01:34:16,166 --> 01:34:18,634
You know? Nothing.

1116
01:34:18,966 --> 01:34:21,799
Jenny, do you know what l need?
l need something very simple.

1117
01:34:21,886 --> 01:34:25,117
l need a woman. But that's so
difficult for you, isn't it?

1118
01:34:25,206 --> 01:34:26,764
You're so full of competition.

1119
01:34:27,286 --> 01:34:29,641
Do you know how empty it is,
how frustrating it is..

1120
01:34:29,726 --> 01:34:32,035
..to reach out for something and
then you find it isn't there?

1121
01:34:33,286 --> 01:34:35,641
To feel that someone is with you.

1122
01:34:37,286 --> 01:34:39,277
David, don't you think that l am?

1123
01:34:39,806 --> 01:34:41,762
Don't you think that l
am in spite of myself?

1124
01:34:41,846 --> 01:34:45,725
- Haven't l tried everything? - Yes,
you have tried. You've split a gut.

1125
01:34:47,046 --> 01:34:50,641
lt's so hard for you. l know.
lt's so hard for both of us.

1126
01:34:53,086 --> 01:34:54,724
All right, you say my work is..

1127
01:34:54,806 --> 01:34:56,717
..the most important thing
in my life. lt is.

1128
01:34:56,806 --> 01:34:58,956
But that's the way l am.
l can't help it.

1129
01:34:59,046 --> 01:35:01,958
And whoever shares my life is just
going to have to put up with that.

1130
01:35:02,126 --> 01:35:04,356
She's going to have to
live a life for me.

1131
01:35:05,286 --> 01:35:08,198
Jenny, l know this sounds
selfish, but it's true.

1132
01:35:17,806 --> 01:35:19,637
We're not gonna go on
together, are we?

1133
01:35:22,806 --> 01:35:24,034
Are we?

1134
01:35:32,206 --> 01:35:33,355
David?

1135
01:35:40,286 --> 01:35:41,639
Come in.

1136
01:35:55,646 --> 01:35:57,045
l would have come to you.

1137
01:35:57,286 --> 01:35:59,356
Well, they said you
weren't feeling well.

1138
01:35:59,446 --> 01:36:01,641
l'm just tired, that's all.

1139
01:36:01,806 --> 01:36:03,637
- Were you sleeping? - No.

1140
01:36:05,046 --> 01:36:08,118
Don't you know it's very unhealthy
to sleep with your clothes on?

1141
01:36:08,206 --> 01:36:09,798
- Where are they? - What?

1142
01:36:11,046 --> 01:36:13,560
- Where are they? - What are you
looking for? - Where are..

1143
01:36:13,646 --> 01:36:15,716
Stop rifling through my things.

1144
01:36:16,206 --> 01:36:18,640
Here they are. Put them on.

1145
01:36:19,206 --> 01:36:20,878
Come on. Put them on.

1146
01:36:27,206 --> 01:36:29,276
And l'll read to you
until you sleep.

1147
01:36:34,286 --> 01:36:37,642
Some pretty risqu? literature
you've got here.

1148
01:36:39,446 --> 01:36:43,724
'Natural Resistance' and
'Clinical Medicine.'

1149
01:36:45,806 --> 01:36:48,115
'Researches on Rheumatism.'

1150
01:36:49,206 --> 01:36:50,798
'Diseases.. '

1151
01:37:11,046 --> 01:37:12,638
l don't know why l'm so tired.

1152
01:37:12,726 --> 01:37:16,162
Why, yes, of course. Well, that's
the way it is sometimes.

1153
01:37:24,166 --> 01:37:25,645
The woodcarver died.

1154
01:37:26,566 --> 01:37:27,965
Yes, l know.

1155
01:37:28,206 --> 01:37:30,720
l have been unable to
accept death. Never.

1156
01:37:31,566 --> 01:37:33,284
No matter how many
times l've seen it.

1157
01:37:33,566 --> 01:37:35,955
l always feel as though
l'm responsible.

1158
01:37:37,446 --> 01:37:38,640
Now..

1159
01:37:39,206 --> 01:37:40,764
..let's see what we've got here.

1160
01:37:47,206 --> 01:37:51,802
The dissolute Lady Chatterley sat
waiting for the gardener to enter.

1161
01:37:52,566 --> 01:37:57,640
He entered, stopping for a moment,
sensing someone in the room.

1162
01:37:57,726 --> 01:38:00,957
His muscles sinewy in the moonlight.

1163
01:38:01,766 --> 01:38:06,044
She spoke his name softly. The
gardener went over to her.

1164
01:38:06,206 --> 01:38:08,356
He kissed Lady Chatterley..

1165
01:38:08,566 --> 01:38:12,957
..with a kiss such as she had
never been given before.

1166
01:38:13,126 --> 01:38:17,722
Her arms were waiting for him,
both resisting and demanding.

1167
01:38:18,046 --> 01:38:23,166
'Jonathan, ' she said, 'Jonathan,
darling, you are violating me.'

1168
01:38:23,246 --> 01:38:24,804
Where did you get that?

1169
01:38:32,206 --> 01:38:33,719
You're so strange.

1170
01:38:34,886 --> 01:38:38,959
Sometimes you're so bitter. Then
you're soft and warm, like a child.

1171
01:38:40,726 --> 01:38:42,045
l'm just a woman.

1172
01:38:43,206 --> 01:38:44,639
Lie back.

1173
01:38:48,046 --> 01:38:49,957
There's three days to Tenerife.

1174
01:38:52,166 --> 01:38:53,281
l know.

1175
01:38:55,366 --> 01:38:57,800
What will your treatment be like
for you there? Do you know?

1176
01:38:58,566 --> 01:38:59,965
Will you be imprisoned?

1177
01:39:02,646 --> 01:39:05,638
lt will be some kind of an
imprisonment, l imagine.

1178
01:39:06,646 --> 01:39:09,956
But you mustn't think of me
sleeping on a stone floor..

1179
01:39:10,046 --> 01:39:12,116
..and living on bread and water.

1180
01:39:13,046 --> 01:39:14,764
This is not my style.

1181
01:39:21,446 --> 01:39:22,720
Now..

1182
01:39:24,046 --> 01:39:25,638
Now l'm going to read to you..

1183
01:39:25,726 --> 01:39:27,717
..from this book exactly
the way it's written.

1184
01:39:27,806 --> 01:39:30,718
lf this doesn't put you to sleep,
nothing ever will.

1185
01:39:30,806 --> 01:39:33,957
The liver is a large,
glandular organ..

1186
01:39:34,046 --> 01:39:38,119
..irregularly shaped and
of reddish-brown color.

1187
01:41:02,286 --> 01:41:03,639
Come on.

1188
01:41:06,206 --> 01:41:08,720
- Please come with me to the table.
- No. l've done enough.

1189
01:41:08,806 --> 01:41:11,639
You just have to take it
from here on by yourself.

1190
01:41:11,726 --> 01:41:13,762
- Are you sure l look all right?
- You look lovely.

1191
01:41:13,846 --> 01:41:15,802
Now, go on.

1192
01:41:24,766 --> 01:41:25,960
Good evening.

1193
01:41:26,366 --> 01:41:27,719
Good evening.

1194
01:41:43,046 --> 01:41:44,161
Hello.

1195
01:41:44,286 --> 01:41:45,355
Hello.

1196
01:41:45,446 --> 01:41:46,640
Waiter.

1197
01:41:47,046 --> 01:41:50,038
l would like one bottle
of champagne, please.

1198
01:41:50,646 --> 01:41:51,965
Would you like to join me?

1199
01:41:52,366 --> 01:41:55,119
Why not? What are we celebrating?

1200
01:42:02,886 --> 01:42:04,114
Quarrel?

1201
01:42:05,206 --> 01:42:06,639
lt's over.

1202
01:42:09,206 --> 01:42:10,639
l'm sorry.

1203
01:42:22,126 --> 01:42:25,641
Will you excuse me? l have
to go to the bridge.

1204
01:42:33,046 --> 01:42:34,365
Do you want to dance?

1205
01:42:35,886 --> 01:42:37,035
No.

1206
01:42:37,886 --> 01:42:39,285
No, not this time.

1207
01:42:39,766 --> 01:42:40,960
Thank you.

1208
01:42:43,286 --> 01:42:46,278
l think l'm going to
go to my cabin..

1209
01:42:46,366 --> 01:42:50,723
..because for me, a little
German music goes a long way.

1210
01:42:57,446 --> 01:42:59,164
Don't be embarrassed.

1211
01:42:59,646 --> 01:43:01,159
Nobody is watching.

1212
01:43:03,206 --> 01:43:04,719
Will l see you later?

1213
01:43:06,206 --> 01:43:07,639
Later.

1214
01:43:30,646 --> 01:43:31,795
Herr Freytag?

1215
01:43:32,566 --> 01:43:33,965
Herr Freytag!

1216
01:43:37,286 --> 01:43:39,959
l want to tell you how sorry l am.

1217
01:43:42,806 --> 01:43:45,718
l wanted to tell you that
with all my heart.

1218
01:43:47,566 --> 01:43:48,965
Heart?

1219
01:43:49,206 --> 01:43:51,640
You have no hearts. Any of you.

1220
01:43:53,446 --> 01:43:56,722
l'm sorry. l've no right
to be rude to you.

1221
01:43:58,046 --> 01:44:01,197
l have no right to
be rude to anybody.

1222
01:44:03,166 --> 01:44:05,043
You must be very much in love..

1223
01:44:05,126 --> 01:44:08,118
