react to that music.

1255
01:46:29,446 --> 01:46:30,640
Schmaltz.

1256
01:46:31,206 --> 01:46:33,356
Tell me, Glocken, now honestly.

1257
01:46:33,446 --> 01:46:36,040
When you hear that music
wherever you are..

1258
01:46:36,126 --> 01:46:38,959
..don't you have a special
feeling about being a German?

1259
01:46:40,126 --> 01:46:42,356
l'll tell you now
Lowenthal honestly.

1260
01:46:42,446 --> 01:46:44,641
When l hear that music
wherever l am..

1261
01:46:44,726 --> 01:46:47,115
..l have a special feeling
about being a dwarf.

1262
01:46:49,766 --> 01:46:54,203
l remember being thousands of miles
from home in a theater in New York.

1263
01:46:54,366 --> 01:46:58,723
They put on a picture of the
funeral of the Kaiserin Viktoria.

1264
01:46:59,206 --> 01:47:03,643
That good woman. How much
she meant to all of us.

1265
01:47:06,046 --> 01:47:07,764
You are German, aren't you?

1266
01:47:08,646 --> 01:47:12,036
You are the most German
person l have ever met.

1267
01:47:13,966 --> 01:47:15,797
l want to show you something.

1268
01:47:16,046 --> 01:47:17,877
l take it out every
once in a while..

1269
01:47:17,966 --> 01:47:20,719
..and look at it when
l want to feel good.

1270
01:47:22,726 --> 01:47:25,638
Why, the Order of the lron Cross!

1271
01:47:26,126 --> 01:47:27,559
Second class.

1272
01:47:29,046 --> 01:47:30,957
And a war hero, besides.

1273
01:47:33,166 --> 01:47:37,045
You may be the biggest fool
on this whole boat.

1274
01:47:39,886 --> 01:47:41,160
Why do you say that?

1275
01:47:42,566 --> 01:47:44,796
Where have you been
during this voyage?

1276
01:47:46,046 --> 01:47:49,356
Do you think this boat is a cross
section of the German people?

1277
01:47:50,166 --> 01:47:51,281
No!

1278
01:47:51,366 --> 01:47:54,642
You don't know the average
German the way l know him.

1279
01:47:54,726 --> 01:47:58,036
The people that produced a Goethe,
a Beethoven and a Bach..

1280
01:47:58,126 --> 01:47:59,878
..are not to be
sneezed at, you know?

1281
01:47:59,966 --> 01:48:03,276
50% of the people who produced a
Goethe, a Beethoven and a Bach..

1282
01:48:03,366 --> 01:48:06,119
..voted for Rieber's party last
week. - Forty-four percent.

1283
01:48:07,206 --> 01:48:10,118
Lowenthal, you are blind!
You're absolutely blind!

1284
01:48:10,206 --> 01:48:12,766
You can't see what's going on
in front of your own face.

1285
01:48:12,966 --> 01:48:14,365
What do you mean?

1286
01:48:15,646 --> 01:48:20,117
You mean this business about the
Jews? You don't understand us.

1287
01:48:20,286 --> 01:48:23,164
The German Jew is something special.

1288
01:48:23,246 --> 01:48:26,363
We are Germans first
and Jews second.

1289
01:48:27,206 --> 01:48:31,722
We have done so much for Germany.
Germany has done so much for us.

1290
01:48:31,806 --> 01:48:35,719
A little patience. A little
goodwill. lt works itself out.

1291
01:48:35,886 --> 01:48:39,356
Listen, there are nearly a
million Jews in Germany.

1292
01:48:39,446 --> 01:48:42,722
