1379
01:58:03,766 --> 01:58:06,280
l thought you weren't bothering
with that cheapskate.

1380
01:58:06,366 --> 01:58:09,563
l have planned something very
interesting for that cheapskate.

1381
01:58:09,646 --> 01:58:14,117
l gave him the cabin of that snotty
American bitch, Mrs. Treadwell.

1382
02:00:23,126 --> 02:00:24,718
l think you are mad.

1383
02:00:25,286 --> 02:00:29,199
l made some inquiries. They would
let me stay on the island.

1384
02:00:29,886 --> 02:00:31,638
l would be able to take care of her.

1385
02:00:32,046 --> 02:00:34,719
l understand your feeling about
her, her helplessness.

1386
02:00:34,806 --> 02:00:38,037
- But to give up everything.
- What would l be giving up?

1387
02:00:39,566 --> 02:00:41,716
- What would l be giving
up? - Your life!

1388
02:00:41,806 --> 02:00:44,957
My life. My life is obligations.

1389
02:00:45,646 --> 02:00:47,955
Obligation to nothing
that's real to me.

1390
02:00:48,286 --> 02:00:51,358
This woman.. this woman over there
in the cabin, she's real to me.

1391
02:00:51,446 --> 02:00:53,562
l know it sounds strange.

1392
02:00:54,206 --> 02:00:57,118
But she's the only real thing
that has happened to me.

1393
02:00:57,206 --> 02:00:59,879
Willy you have heard of shipboard
romances, haven't you?

1394
02:00:59,966 --> 02:01:02,116
